      {
        "paragraph_index": 1,
        "text": "Approximate pH for onset of precipitation\n- Oxalate is largely present as L2− (C2O4²−) once pH exceeds pKa2. Using the SRD‑46 pKa2 ≈ 3.8, the L2− fraction rises steeply above pH ~4.  \n- With millimolar Ca and total oxalate, the ionic product [Ca2+][C2O4²−] will exceed the COM Ksp (pKsp ≈ 8.6, Ksp ≈ 2.5×10^−9) soon after L2− becomes a major species. Accounting for some CaC2O4(aq) complexation (log β1 ≈ 3.3) that buffers free ions, the practical onset is slightly higher than pKa2.",
